[Freeport (2010, population 7879) is a town on the Atlantic coast in Cumberland County, Maine, United States, known for its numerous outlet stores, about 17 miles north of Portland, the most populous city in Maine and the seat of Cumberland County (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cumberland_County,_Maine). A map showing the location of Freeport can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Portland,+ME/Freeport,+ME+04032. - Mod.ML]

